Property Plotting: Aligning Content in Edge Cases

	align-self: used to align individual flex items by overriding the align-items value. The default value is stretch and it accepts:
		stretch, flex-start, flex-end, center, baseline.

		If you use "stretch" the contents will stretch across the cross axis.

		If you use "center" the content will center on the cross axis.

	Controlling Page Layout with flex-wrap
		With flex wrap each item defaults to stretch.

		NOTE align items doesn't control wrapped items.

	Align-content: used to align wrapped flex items. The default value is stretch and it accepts: stretch, flex-start, flex-end, center, space-between, space-around.	

